This is really a new type of warfare we see in the War in Ukraine. I have no doubt that the war planers and other experts from Pentagon are working around the clock on developing new tactics, strategy and doctrine while extracting stuff for the weapon developers to take notice of during the R&D process of developing new weapons..
A lot of lessons have been learned during the last 8 months...

Its that everywhere i find the most stubborn mental propaganda. I just watch it, see it for what it is. I think politics are not of any concern on the battlefield. Its guys who are committed, and Ukraine likely has the highest moral, and the best training. Your channel does not have the mental issues, but both sides... Well each its own beast.. 

The Chechens they are always there when there is war. Last time they fought against Russia, now they are with Russia. If things settle they always want to make friends, its strange, i think they want to take over Russia, but with a different sort of approach, also they set their teeth in Ukraine. Megalomaniacs? Maybe. Probably not too many in your territory. Who knows?? 

The fleeing of Boris was quick, it only took a couple of artillery rounds. 

With a map and pinpointing the enemy positions you can pursue the enemy with artillery. Of course munitions are not unlimited, and neither is range. That grad shooting was a couple of kilometers further. I dont know the situation on the ground. 

Well, you are a honest man. 

Good luck! 

Greetings,


Jeff
